---
import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { graph, breadcrumbSchema, canonical } from '@lib/seo';
const crumbs = [{ name: 'Home', url: '/' }, { name: 'How we test', url: '/how-we-test/' }];
const schema = graph(breadcrumbSchema(crumbs.map((c) => ({ name: c.name, url: canonical(c.url) }))));
---
<Base title="How We Test Tower Fans" description="Our tower fan testing process, how we measure airflow, noise, running costs and everyday usability to rank the best tower fans in the UK." path="/how-we-test/" schema={schema}>
  <section class="bg-breeze-mesh border-b border-breeze-100"><div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-6 pb-10"><Breadcrumbs crumbs={crumbs} /><h1 class="mt-5 text-4xl sm:text-5xl">How we test tower fans</h1><p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink-500">The same checks, applied to every fan, so our rankings are fair and comparable.</p></div></section>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 prose-tf">
    <p>Every tower fan we recommend goes through the same hands-on assessment. We don't rely on manufacturer spec sheets, we test what it's actually like to live with.</p>
    <h2>Airflow and cooling</h2>
    <p>We measure how far each fan can push usable airflow, how wide its oscillation covers a room, and whether the higher speeds add real cooling or just noise. A fan that only feels powerful from 30cm away isn't much use in a living room.</p>
    <h2>Noise</h2>
    <p>Noise is the number-one complaint about tower fans. We check volume at the lowest useful setting (the one you'd actually sleep with) and at maximum, and we listen for rattles, motor whine and bearing hum that spec sheets never mention.</p>
    <h2>Running cost</h2>
    <p>We calculate real running costs in pence per hour at current UK energy prices, based on each fan's measured power draw, so you know what it costs to run overnight, not just what it costs to buy.</p>
    <h2>Features and usability</h2>
    <p>Timers, remotes, app control, sleep modes, display dimming, ease of cleaning and how stable the fan is on carpet all feed into the score. These are the details that decide whether you'll still be happy with a fan two summers from now.</p>
    <h2>Scoring</h2>
    <p>Each fan gets a star rating out of five that blends these factors, weighted towards the things most people care about: cooling, noise and value. We re-test and re-score as ranges and prices change.</p>
  </div>
</Base>
